In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 7 through October 13, 2012, as Fire Prevention Week. He emphasizes the importance of taking steps to protect ourselves, our families, and our communities from fires. The President encourages Americans to install and maintain smoke alarms, test smoke alarm batteries regularly, and follow safe practices in the kitchen and when using electrical appliances. He also urges families to develop and practice a fire escape plan. The article highlights the need for individuals in wildfire-prone areas to take action by clearing flammable vegetation, preparing an emergency supply kit, and sharing evacuation routes and communication plans with their families. The President expresses gratitude to firefighters for their service and pays tribute to those who have lost their lives in the line of duty. He calls on all Americans to participate in Fire Prevention Week and renew their efforts to prevent fires.